  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intraabdominal infection require rapid care management including antibiotic therapy and
      source control. Morbidity and mortality associated with Intraabdominal infections remain
      high. French recommendations have been edited in 2000 further updated in 2014. Delay in
      diagnosis and surgery can lead to worsened outcomes. However, little data are available on
      early community-acquired intraabdominal infections management to identify risk factors of
      inadequate management.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
